"repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/alice-i-cecile/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/alice-i-cecile/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/alice-i-cecile/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":123,"closed_issues":92,"state":"open","created_at":"2025-06-16T16:30:51Z","updated_at":"2025-11-09T21:03:49Z","due_on":null,"closed_at":null},"comments":0,"created_at":"2025-10-12T09:18:17Z","updated_at":"2025-10-17T18:11:27Z","closed_at":"2025-10-17T18:11:26Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## How can Bevy's documentation be improved?\n\nThe controls here:\n\nhttps://dev-docs.bevy.org/bevy/feathers/controls/index.html\n\nFor example button: \n\nhttps://dev-docs.bevy.org/bevy/feathers/controls/fn.button.html\n\nshould specify in docs which event (or events) they emit when interacted with.\n\nCurrently the only way to know is to look at the feathers example to see which events are observed close to some control, for example: `On<ValueChange<bool>>`, `On<Activate>`, `On<ValueChange<f32>>`, etc.\n\nIdeally each control had a snippet in the docs to the effect of \n\n```rust\n// From the feathers example, a relatively minimal snippet of how to observe checkbox interactions\n(\n    checkbox(\n        InteractionDisabled,\n        Spawn((Text::new(\"Disabled\"), ThemedText))\n    ),\n    observe(|_change: On<ValueChange<bool>>| {\n        warn!(\"Disabled checkbox clicked!\");\n    })\n),\n```","closed_by":{"login":"alice-i-cecile","id":3579909,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1Nzk5MDk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3579909?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/alice-i-cecile","html_url":"https://github.com/alice-i-cecile","followers